---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Nurses | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Nurses working internationally, covering nursing careers abroad, healthcare facility positions, and global nursing opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Nurses";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Nurses working abroad, providing care internationally, and pursuing careers across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/nurse-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/nurse-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Nursing Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Nurses provide essential patient care across healthcare settings, from bedside care to specialized clinical roles. International nursing careers offer opportunities to work in different healthcare systems, experience diverse medical practices, and address nursing shortages in countries worldwide.
      </p>
      <p>
        International nursing opportunities exist through healthcare recruitment agencies, direct hospital hiring programs, humanitarian organizations, travel nursing agencies, and government-to-government healthcare agreements that facilitate nurse mobility across borders.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Nurses working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Nurses</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Occupational exposure', why: 'Needlestick and infection risk', typical: 'Critical for profession' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Patient care stress', typical: 'Important to include' },
          { need: 'Physical injury coverage', why: 'Patient handling injuries', typical: 'Essential for nurses' },
          { need: 'Professional liability', why: 'Clinical practice protection', typical: 'Verify employer provides' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Career protection', typical: 'Review carefully' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Occupational Hazards</h3>
      <p>
        Nursing involves significant occupational health risks including needlestick injuries, exposure to infectious diseases, and contact with hazardous medications. Coverage for post-exposure prophylaxis and testing is essential for nurses working internationally.
      </p>
      <p>
        Physical demands of patient care—lifting, repositioning, and extended standing—create musculoskeletal injury risks. Many nursing careers end prematurely due to back injuries, making physical injury coverage and disability protection particularly important.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Nursing requires sustained emotional engagement with patients and families during difficult circumstances. Compassion fatigue, burnout, and secondary traumatic stress affect many nurses. Mental health support is valuable for sustaining long-term nursing careers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Hospitals</h3>
      <p>
        Acute care hospital nursing. Hospital benefits typically comprehensive. Structured environment. Hospitals offer stability and career progression.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel Nursing</h3>
      <p>
        Assignment-based nursing positions. Agency benefits variable. High flexibility. Travel nursing offers premium compensation.
      </p>

      <h3>International Clinics</h3>
      <p>
        Outpatient and specialty clinics abroad. Clinic benefits vary. Diverse settings. Clinics offer work-life balance.
      </p>

      <h3>Humanitarian</h3>
      <p>
        NGO and disaster relief nursing. Organization provides coverage. Challenging environments. Humanitarian work offers purpose.
      </p>

      <h3>Private Healthcare</h3>
      <p>
        Private hospitals and clinics. Often premium benefits. International patient populations. Private sector offers compensation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Nurses"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Nurses working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Nurse Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Nursing License</h3>
      <p>
        Home country RN or equivalent. Foundation credential. Essential for any nursing work. License enables practice.
      </p>

      <h3>Country-Specific Registration</h3>
      <p>
        Destination country nursing registration. Process varies significantly. Often requires exams. Registration permits legal practice.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        ICU, OR, emergency, oncology certifications. Specialty credentials. Enhanced opportunities. Certifications demonstrate expertise.
      </p>

      <h3>Language Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Language proficiency for patient care. Often tested requirement. Communication essential. Language enables safe practice.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Exposure Risk</h3>
      <p>
        Bloodborne pathogen exposure. Infectious disease contact. Needle safety critical. Exposure coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Patient lifting and moving. Extended standing. Repetitive tasks. Physical coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Shift Work</h3>
      <p>
        Night shifts and rotating schedules. Sleep disruption. Circadian impact. Shift work affects health.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Burden</h3>
      <p>
        Patient suffering and loss. Family interactions. Moral distress. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Patient Care</h3>
      <p>
        Direct patient care delivery. Assessment and intervention. Care coordination. Patient care is core function.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Medical record maintenance. Care documentation. Legal requirements. Documentation supports care quality.
      </p>

      <h3>Collaboration</h3>
      <p>
        Interdisciplinary teamwork. Physician coordination. Healthcare team communication. Collaboration ensures comprehensive care.
      </p>

      <h3>Advocacy</h3>
      <p>
        Patient advocacy role. Family communication. Care navigation. Advocacy protects patient interests.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Nursing shortages worldwide. Strong international demand. Immigration pathways. Demand creates opportunity.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Staff nurse to charge nurse. Nurse manager. Advanced practice. Education. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Recognition varies by country. Mutual recognition agreements exist. Process can be lengthy. Research destination requirements.
      </p>

      <h3>Compensation</h3>
      <p>
        Varies significantly by country. Gulf states and Western countries higher. Consider cost of living. Evaluate total package.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a nurse considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Credential recognition varies by country. Employer coverage typically provided. Verify occupational exposure coverage. Research licensing requirements thoroughly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do international hospitals provide good coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Generally yes for recruited positions. Benefits part of employment package. Verify specific terms. Large systems typically comprehensive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is occupational exposure covered internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical to verify. Should include post-exposure prophylaxis. Testing coverage important. Essential for nursing practice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about travel nursing internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Agency provides coverage typically. Verify between assignments. Premium compensation. Coverage terms vary by agency.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Should I prioritize disability coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for physical careers. Back injuries common in nursing. Long-term protection important. Consider career sustainability.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong global demand. Nursing shortages widespread. Good immigration pathways. Excellent international opportunities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by researching nursing registration requirements for your target destination. Verify that employer-provided coverage includes occupational exposure protection. Consider mental health support for emotional demands of patient care. Review disability coverage for long-term career protection.
      </p>
      <p>
        Nurses provide essential care to patients worldwide. Your coverage should support demanding healthcare careers—addressing occupational hazards, accommodating shift work, and protecting your health across nursing positions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Nursing Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Nurses working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
